# publish the under-declaring vendor so the producer, consumer, and local project can resolve it
> vendor/publishLocal
# the producer patches a RUNTIME-scoped vendor dep via .options; the patch propagates into the producer's descriptor
# (it would be dropped were the export scope Compile-visible)
> checkPatch
# the consumer links the producer and folds the propagated patch; the unresolvable library fails the link (completeness)
-> consumer/Compile/snxLink
# the local project patches vendor for its OWN link; .options folds into that link too, where the unresolvable library fails it
-> local/Compile/snxLink
